Its okay. You want the biggest possible X86_L1_CACHE_SHIFT for
X86_GENERIC, and it is the one for MPENTIUM4 (128 bytes).
Otherwise you will degrade performance on P4 when running generic kernel.
Regards,
--
Bartlomiej
